      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The consensus among mainstream economists is shifting away from the simplistic \"trickle-down\" theory being a guaranteed mechanism for wealth equalization. Empirical data increasingly suggests that tax cuts heavily favoring capital gains and high earners do not automatically translate into broad-based wage growth. Therefore, the weight of the evidence leans toward the view that these reforms risk widening the wealth gap unless accompanied by significant investments in public goods and social safety nets.",
